label.value: ubiquitin-like FUBI-ribosomal protein eS30 fusion protein

value.value: A protein that is a translation product of the human FAU gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that contains only a single inorganic pyrophosphatase (Pfam:PF00719) domain in eukaryotes.

A ubiquitin-like FUBI-ribosomal protein eS30 fusion protein that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage to yield the N-terminal portion containing the Pfam:PF00240 (ubiquitin) domain. Example: UniProtKB:P62861, 1-74.

An IgA immunoglobulin complex in human that is composed of (in monomeric form) two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the IgA1 isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda) held together by disulfide bonds, and sometimes complexed with J chain or J chain and secretory component. An IgA1 immunoglobulin complex may be embedded in the plasma membrane or present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

definition.value: Category=organism-complex. Requested by=HIPC. Requested by=CL. Note that an IgA1 immunoglobulin complex has the function of antigen binding if a suitable antigen is available.

value.value: An IgA immunoglobulin complex in human that is composed of (in monomeric form) two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the IgA2 isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda) held together by disulfide bonds, and sometimes complexed with J chain or J chain and secretory component. An IgA2 immunoglobulin complex may be embedded in the plasma membrane or present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

definition.value: Category=organism-complex. Requested by=HIPC. Requested by=CL. Note that an IgA2 immunoglobulin complex has the function of antigen binding if a suitable antigen is available.

value.value: An IgA immunoglobulin complex, circulating in human that is composed of (in monomeric form) two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the secretory isoform of the IgA1 isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda), held together by disulfide bonds, sometimes complexed with J chain or J chain and secretory component, and present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

An IgA immunoglobulin complex, circulating in human that is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the secretory isoform of the IgA2 isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda), held together by disulfide bonds, sometimes complexed with J chain or J chain and secretory component, and present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

definition.value: Category=organism-complex. Requested by=HIPC. Requested by=CL. Note: Human circulating IgA2 is only found as a monomeric form.

value.value: An IgA1 immunoglobulin complex in human that is present in the plasma membrane of B cells and is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the membrane-bound isoform of the IgA1 isotype, two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda), and a signaling subunit, a heterodimer of the Ig-alpha and Ig-beta proteins.

An IgA2 immunoglobulin complex in human that is present in the plasma membrane of B cells and is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the membrane-bound isoform of the IgA2 isotype, two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda), and a signaling subunit, a heterodimer of the Ig-alpha and Ig-beta proteins.

An IgA1 immunoglobulin complex, circulating (human) that is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the secretory isoform of the IgA1 isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda), held together by disulfide bonds, and present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.
A protein that contains two copies of a GAF domain (Pfam:PF01590 or Pfam:PF13185) followed by a 3'5'-cyclic nucleotide phosphodiesterase (Pfam:PF00233) domain.
A polymeric immunoglobulin receptor secretory component in human. UniProtKB:P01833, 19-603.

An IgD immunoglobulin complex whose components are encoded in the genome of human. IgD is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the IgD isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda), held together by disulfide bonds. An IgD immunoglobulin complex may be embedded in the plasma membrane or present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

definition.value: Category=organism-complex. Requested by=HIPC. Requested by=CL. Note that an IgD immunoglobulin complex has the function of antigen binding if a suitable antigen is available.

value.value: An IgD immunoglobulin complex, circulating whose components are encoded in the genome of human. Circulating IgD is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the IgD isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda), held together by disulfide bonds, and present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

An IgD B cell receptor complex whose components are encoded in the genome of human. The IgD B cell receptor complex is present in the plasma membrane of B cells and is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the IgD isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda) and a signaling subunit, a heterodimer of the Ig-alpha and Ig-beta proteins.

An IgD immunoglobulin complex, GPI-anchored whose components are encoded in the genome of human. GPI-anchored IgD is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the IgD isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains (kappa or lambda), held together by disulfide bonds, and bound via a GPI-anchor to the plasma membrane of B cells.
A protein that is a translation product of some mRNA produced by a somatically recombined immunoglobulin heavy chain locus.

definition.value: Category=family. Requested by=IEDB. Note: In human, the IgH locus is described by https://www.genenames.org/cgi-bin/genefamilies/set/349. In mouse, the locus is described by MGI:96442.

value.value: A protein that is a translation product of some mRNA produced by a somatically recombined immunoglobulin light chain locus.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: In human, the kappa light chain locus is described by https://www.genenames.org/cgi-bin/genefamilies/set/351, and the lambda light chain locus is described by https://www.genenames.org/cgi-bin/genefamilies/set/353. In mouse, the kappa locus is described by MGI:96494, and the lambda locus is described by MGI:96526.

value.value: An immunoglobulin heavy chain protein in which the constant region is encoded either by the IgA1 gene segment or the IgA2 gene segment.
An IgA heavy chain protein in which the constant region is encoded by the IgA1 gene segment.
An IgA heavy chain protein in which the constant region is encoded by the IgA2 gene segment.
An IgA1 heavy chain protein that is encoded in the genome of human.
